      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i was just looking at some space photos and it just hit me... like we're just these tiny accidents on a speck of dust in an infinite void. eventually everything just goes cold and dark anyway. what's even the point of trying so hard to be \"okay\" or build anything when none of it actually matters in the long run?",
